{"title":"Moving from NYC to Miami: Complete Relocation Guide [2026]","description":"Compare cost of living, housing, taxes, and quality of life when moving from NYC to Miami. Data-driven relocation guide with calculators.","url":"https://urcity.com/compare/moving-from-nyc-to-miami/","content":"\u003ch2 id=\"introduction\"\u003eIntroduction\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMoving from New York City to Miami? You\u0026rsquo;re joining a wave of finance and tech professionals making the same move. Miami offers tropical weather, no state income tax, and a lower cost of living — but the housing market is more competitive than you might expect.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"cost-of-living-comparison\"\u003eCost of Living Comparison\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ctable\u003e\n\t\u003cthead\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eCategory\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eNYC\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eMiami\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eSavings\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\u003c/thead\u003e\n\t\u003ctbody\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eOverall Index\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e187.2\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e145.6\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e-22%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eRent (1BR)\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$3,800/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$2,400/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e-$1,400/mo\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eHome Price\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$750,000\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$520,000\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e-31%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eUtilities\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$150/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$145/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e-3%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eGroceries\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$500/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$420/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e-16%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eTransportation\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$200/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$180/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e-10%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eHealthcare\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$450/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$380/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e-16%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMonthly savings potential: $1,500–$2,000\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"salary-calculator\"\u003eSalary Calculator\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf you make \u003cstrong\u003e$100,000 in NYC\u003c/strong\u003e, you need approximately \u003cstrong\u003e$78,000 in Miami\u003c/strong\u003e to maintain the same standard of living.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"calculator-widget\" id=\"salary-calc\"\u003e\n  \u003ch3\u003eSalary Comparison Calculator\u003c/h3\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"calc-row\"\u003e\n    \u003clabel\u003eCurrent Salary ($)\u003c/label\u003e\n    \u003cinput type=\"number\" id=\"current-salary\" value=\"100000\" min=\"0\" step=\"1000\"\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"calc-row\"\u003e\n    \u003clabel\u003eFrom City\u003c/label\u003e\n    \u003cselect id=\"from-city\"\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"nyc\" selected\u003eNew York City\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"sf\" \u003eSan Francisco\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"la\" \u003eLos Angeles\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"chicago\" \u003eChicago\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"austin-tx\" \u003eAustin\u003c/option\u003e\n    \u003c/select\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"calc-row\"\u003e\n    \u003clabel\u003eTo City\u003c/label\u003e\n    \u003cselect id=\"to-city\"\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"austin-tx\" \u003eAustin\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"nyc\" \u003eNew York City\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"sf\" \u003eSan Francisco\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"la\" \u003eLos Angeles\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"chicago\" \u003eChicago\u003c/option\u003e\n    \u003c/select\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cbutton class=\"btn btn-primary\" onclick=\"calculateSalary()\"\u003eCalculate\u003c/button\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"calc-result\" id=\"salary-result\" style=\"display:none;\"\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003eYou need \u003cstrong id=\"needed-salary\"\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e in \u003cspan id=\"target-city-name\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e to maintain the same standard of living.\u003c/p\u003e\n    \u003cp id=\"salary-difference\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cscript\u003e\nfunction calculateSalary() {\n  const salary = parseFloat(document.getElementById('current-salary').value);\n  const fromCity = document.getElementById('from-city').value;\n  const toCity = document.getElementById('to-city').value;\n  \n  const colIndex = {\n    'nyc': 187.2,\n    'sf': 269.3,\n    'la': 173.3,\n    'chicago': 110.8,\n    'austin-tx': 119.3\n  };\n  \n  const cityNames = {\n    'nyc': 'New York City',\n    'sf': 'San Francisco',\n    'la': 'Los Angeles',\n    'chicago': 'Chicago',\n    'austin-tx': 'Austin'\n  };\n  \n  const neededSalary = Math.round(salary * (colIndex[toCity] / colIndex[fromCity]));\n  const diff = salary - neededSalary;\n  \n  document.getElementById('needed-salary').textContent = '$' + neededSalary.toLocaleString();\n  document.getElementById('target-city-name').textContent = cityNames[toCity];\n  \n  const diffEl = document.getElementById('salary-difference');\n  if (diff \u003e 0) {\n    diffEl.innerHTML = 'You would save \u003cstrong\u003e$' + diff.toLocaleString() + '/year\u003c/strong\u003e by moving.';\n    diffEl.className = 'savings-positive';\n  } else if (diff \u003c 0) {\n    diffEl.innerHTML = 'You would need \u003cstrong\u003e$' + Math.abs(diff).toLocaleString() + '/year more\u003c/strong\u003e to maintain your lifestyle.';\n    diffEl.className = 'savings-negative';\n  } else {\n    diffEl.textContent = 'Cost of living is roughly the same.';\n  }\n  \n  document.getElementById('salary-result').style.display = 'block';\n}\n\u003c/script\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"housing-market\"\u003eHousing Market\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"nyc\"\u003eNYC\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMedian home: $750,000\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMedian rent (1BR): $3,800/month\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePrice per sq ft: $1,200\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"miami\"\u003eMiami\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMedian home: $520,000\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMedian rent (1BR): $2,400/month\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePrice per sq ft: $380\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMiami housing is cheaper than NYC but more expensive than most people expect.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"taxes\"\u003eTaxes\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ctable\u003e\n\t\u003cthead\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eTax Type\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eNYC\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eMiami\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\u003c/thead\u003e\n\t\u003ctbody\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eState Income Tax\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e6.85%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e0%\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eCity Income Tax\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e3.876%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e0%\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eSales Tax\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e8.875%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e7%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eProperty Tax\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e~0.88%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e~0.94%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAnnual tax savings on $100K salary: ~$10,700\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"climate\"\u003eClimate\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ctable\u003e\n\t\u003cthead\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003e\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eNYC\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eMiami\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\u003c/thead\u003e\n\t\u003ctbody\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eSummer High\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e84°F\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e91°F\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eWinter Low\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e26°F\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e60°F\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eSunny Days\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e234\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e248\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eHumidity\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eVery High\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTrade-off:\u003c/strong\u003e Hot, humid summers in Miami, but no more brutal NYC winters.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"culture--lifestyle\"\u003eCulture \u0026amp; Lifestyle\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"what-youll-miss-from-nyc\"\u003eWhat You\u0026rsquo;ll Miss from NYC\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e24/7 everything\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWorld-class museums and Broadway\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExtensive subway system\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFour distinct seasons\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDiversity of neighborhoods\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"what-youll-gain-in-miami\"\u003eWhat You\u0026rsquo;ll Gain in Miami\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBeaches year-round\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eLatin culture and cuisine\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eNo state income tax\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eOutdoor lifestyle\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eArt Basel and Wynwood\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"best-neighborhoods-in-miami-for-nyc-transplants\"\u003eBest Neighborhoods in Miami for NYC Transplants\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBrickell\u003c/strong\u003e — Financial district, most like Manhattan\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWynwood\u003c/strong\u003e — Artsy, trendy, like Williamsburg\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSouth Beach\u003c/strong\u003e — Iconic, touristy, like Times Square but beachy\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCoconut Grove\u003c/strong\u003e — Laid-back, like the West Village\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"is-it-worth-it\"\u003eIs It Worth It?\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eYes — if you love warm weather and don\u0026rsquo;t mind humidity.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe tax savings alone ($10,000+/year) make the move financially compelling. Miami\u0026rsquo;s growing finance and tech scenes mean career opportunities are expanding. The main drawbacks are humidity, traffic, and a less walkable city.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDisclaimer:\u003c/strong\u003e All cost of living figures, housing prices, tax estimates, and savings calculations on this page are provided for informational purposes only and do not constitute financial, legal, tax, or real estate advice. Actual costs and savings will vary based on your specific circumstances, lifestyle, income, deductions, and local market conditions. URCity and Northshore Press are not financial advisors, tax professionals, or real estate agents. Always consult qualified professionals before making relocation or financial decisions.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"frequently-asked-questions\"\u003eFrequently Asked Questions\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"is-miami-safe\"\u003eIs Miami safe?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eIt depends on the neighborhood.\u003c/strong\u003e Like any major city, some areas are safer than others. Brickell, Coral Gables, and Coconut Grove are generally safe. Research neighborhoods before moving.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"do-i-need-a-car-in-miami\"\u003eDo I need a car in Miami?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eYes.\u003c/strong\u003e Miami is not walkable or subway-dependent like NYC. You\u0026rsquo;ll need a car for most daily activities.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"hows-the-job-market\"\u003eHow\u0026rsquo;s the job market?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGrowing.\u003c/strong\u003e Miami has become \u0026ldquo;Wall Street South\u0026rdquo; with major finance firms relocating. Tech is also growing rapidly.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"whats-hurricane-season-like\"\u003eWhat\u0026rsquo;s hurricane season like?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eJune–November.\u003c/strong\u003e Most buildings are hurricane-resistant. Get renters/homeowners insurance and follow evacuation orders if needed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"data-sources\"\u003eData Sources\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCost of living: Council for Community and Economic Research (C2ER)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHousing data: Zillow Research\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTax data: Tax Foundation\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMigration data: IRS Statistics of Income\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eLast updated: June 28, 2026\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n"}